Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Book Appointment, Validate Available Time Slots
   Explanation: The use case "Validate Available Time Slots" is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Book Appointment"). It is not associated with any actor directly, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any other use case, and is not involved in any generalization relationship. "Validate Available Time Slots" represents a sub-step of the booking process rather than a complete, independently meaningful service observable to any actor. This is a classic functional decomposition where the base use case's internal logic has been improperly broken out into a separate inclusion use case that provides no standalone value to any user.
